    "summary": "I am a PhD candidate in the department of econometrics and operations research of Tilburg University.  My research focuses on the development of new econometric and statistical expertise and methods for data-driven banking and insurance. My thesis was funded by the Dutch Organisation for Scientific Research (NWO) and was part of a larger collaboration between Tilburg University, Eindhoven University of Technology, Rabobank and Achmea. In turn I worked with different data science teams of the latter company where I focused on profit-driven applications of predictive analytics and in particular on fraud detection in non-life insurance.\n\nPrior to that I was a front office quantitative research intern at ING Brussels, Belgium and a financial services research associate at Vlerick Business School.\n\nI studied mathematics in Toulouse, France and quantitative finance at the Solvay Brussels School of Economics and Management.",
